	<section>
		<h2>FAQ</h2>
		<dl>
			<dt>1. What is the Blood Bank Management System?</dt>
			<dd>The Blood Bank Management System is a software application
				designed to manage and automate various tasks related to blood
				donation, storage, distribution, and inventory management within a
				blood bank or blood donation center.</dd>

			<dt>2. How can I donate blood using this system?</dt>
			<dd>To donate blood, you typically need to register as a donor
				with the blood bank. You can either visit the blood bank in person
				or check if they have an online registration portal. Once
				registered, you can schedule an appointment to donate blood through
				the system.</dd>

			<dt>3. Can I request blood through this system?</dt>
			<dd>Yes, if you are in need of blood, you can request it through
				the Blood Bank Management System. You will need to provide necessary
				details such as blood type, quantity required, and patient
				information. The system will then search for matching donors and
				facilitate the blood donation process.</dd>

			<dt>4. How does the system ensure the safety of donated blood?</dt>
			<dd>The system maintains detailed records of each blood
				donation, including donor information, blood type, screening tests,
				and storage conditions. Before blood is distributed, it undergoes
				rigorous testing for infectious diseases to ensure its safety.
				Additionally, the system tracks the expiry dates of blood units to
				prevent the use of expired blood.</dd>

			<dt>5. Can I track my blood donation history through this
				system?</dt>
			<dd>Yes, registered donors can log in to the system to view
				their donation history, including the dates of donations, blood
				types donated, and any special notes or feedback provided by the
				blood bank staff.</dd>

			<dt>6. How secure is the data stored in the Blood Bank
				Management System?</dt>
			<dd>The system employs various security measures such as
				encryption, access controls, and regular data backups to ensure the
				confidentiality, integrity, and availability of donor and patient
				information.</dd>
		</dl>
